Class Planet

java.lang.Object
org.example.galaxy_trucker.Model.Cards.Planet
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Planet extends Object implements Serializable
The Planet class represents a planet with associated goods and an occupancy status indicating whether a player has chosen the planet. This class is serializable and utilizes JSON annotations for data exchange.

  • Constructor Details

    • Planet

      public Planet()
      Constructs a default instance of the Planet class. Initializes the planet with no goods and as unoccupied.

  • Method Details

    • getGoods

      public ArrayList<Goods> getGoods()
      Retrieves the list of goods associated with the planet. The goods represent resources or items available on the planet, which conform to the Goods interface.
      Returns:
      an ArrayList containing all the goods present on the planet

    • isOccupied

      public boolean isOccupied()
      Checks whether the planet is currently occupied by a player.
      Returns:
      true if the planet is occupied by a player, false otherwise.

    • setGoods

      public void setGoods(ArrayList<Goods> goods)
      Updates the list of goods associated with the planet. The goods represent resources or items available, which conform to the Goods interface.
      Parameters:
      goods - the new list of goods to be associated with the planet

    • setOccupied

      public void setOccupied(Player occupied)
      Sets the player occupying the planet. If a player is specified, the planet is marked as occupied by that player. Passing null indicates that the planet is no longer occupied.
      Parameters:
      occupied - the player to occupy the planet, or null to mark it as unoccupied

    • getOccupied

      public Player getOccupied()
      Retrieves the player occupying the planet. If the planet is unoccupied, this method returns null.
      Returns:
      the Player object representing the player occupying the planet, or null if the planet is unoccupied
